"pages": [
        {
	"type": "text",
	"anchor": "thirst",
	"text": "Not only do you have to keep yourself fed, but you also need to keep yourself hydrated.$(br2)There are a handful of water options, and if all else fails, you can drink from any water source with an empty hand and shift right clicking."
        },
        {
	"type": "text",
	"text": "$(br)There are two aspects to keeping yourself hydrated: thirst and hydration.$(br2)Thirst is the actual water droplets (2 thirst being 1 droplet), much like your food shanks.$(br2)Hydration is how fast your thirst drops, much like saturation."
        },
        {
	"type": "text",
	"text": "$(br)Be careful of the things you drink though. If they are not poisoned, you could get a poisoned effect, like hunger, that drains your thirst.$(br2)The following pages will list the things you can drink, and the amounts they recover."
        },
